description:
The current code:
  for row in words.chunks(4) {
      let start = words.iter().position(|w| w == &row[0]).unwrap_or(0) + 1;
      ...
  }
This is O(N) per chunk to find the start index, when the index is already implicit in the chunk position. It also triggers the correctness bug (nie-52o.1) when words repeat.

Suggested rewrite:
  for (chunk_idx, row) in words.chunks(4).enumerate() {
      let start = chunk_idx * 4 + 1;
      for (j, word) in row.iter().enumerate() {
          print!("{:2}. {:<12}", start + j, word);
      }
      println!();
  }
This is O(1) per chunk, avoids the duplicate-word bug, and makes the intent obvious.
